claim.claim-text:
A luminaire comprising:
a tube-shaped housing (10) extending in a first direction (X), the housing (10) including an opening (14) formed continuously in the first direction (X) and a pair of grooves (15) formed respectively in the vicinity of both edge portions of the opening (14) in a second direction (Y) orthogonal to the first direction (X) and extending in the first direction (X);
a mounting plate (30) including a light source mounting plate (31) facing the opening (14) and a power supply mounting plate (32) facing an inner wall of the housing (10), and provided in the interior of the housing (10);
a light source module (40) including a substrate (41) provided on the light source mounting plate (31) and a light-emitting element (42) mounted on the substrate (41) with a light-emitting surface (42a) thereof oriented toward the opening (14);
a power supply unit (50) provided on the power supply mounting plate (32); and
a flexible and translucent cover (60) including a pair of flange portions (63) engaging respectively with the pair of grooves (15) and configured to close the opening (14),
the light-emitting surface (42a) of the light-emitting element (42) being located on the opening (14) side with respect to the flange portion, and
gaps (80) being formed between the flange portions (63) and the substrate (41), and the flange portions (63) being slidable between the grooves (15) and the substrate (41) through the gaps (80) by bending the cover (60).
